## PostgreSQL (Layer 3 — environment)

- Run it locally via Docker/compose for parity with production. Pin the major version.
- All schema changes go through **migrations** (never hand-edit prod). Migrations are reviewed and reversible.
- Connection via env vars (`DATABASE_URL`); never commit credentials. Least-privilege DB users.
- Index for real query patterns; avoid N+1; use transactions for multi-step writes.

> For version/feature specifics, query **context7** (or the PostgreSQL docs).
